   The annual Booker ballyhoo got going yesterday
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   when the judges for this year's #20,000 prize for British (and Commonwealth) fiction announced the shortlist.
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   The prize is no longer the richest literary award
  </a>
  <a href="#4" id="4">
   but it guarantees great prestige and sales for the winner
  </a>
  <a href="#5" id="5">
   and brings the novel to public attention.
  </a>
  <a href="#6" id="6">
   Critics say the brouhaha distorts
  </a>
  <a href="#7" id="7">
   the annual fiction industry and the intense media hype of the shortlisted authors does a disservice to other gifted but unlisted authors.
  </a>
  <a href="#8" id="8">
